Hey everyone! I'm working on a new ElizaOS plugin and could use some feedback
That sounds awesome! What kind of plugin are you building? I'd love to help test it
It's a plugin for automated code review! It analyzes pull requests and suggests improvements using AI
Oh wow, that could be really useful! How does it integrate with GitHub?
It uses webhooks to listen for PR events, then the agent analyzes the diff and posts review comments. I'm using the GitHub provider from ElizaOS core
That's really smart! Can you share the code? I'd love to see how you're parsing the diffs
Sure! I'll push it to my GitHub repo later today. The diff parsing is actually pretty straightforward - I'm using the same library that VS Code uses
This is exactly what our team needs! We've been doing manual code reviews and it takes forever
Happy to help! Once I get it working reliably, I'll publish it as an official ElizaOS plugin

Good morning everyone! I just deployed the new ElizaOS agent to production and it's working great
Awesome! What's the response time looking like?
Really good! Average response time is under 200ms. The caching layer is working perfectly
That's impressive! Are you using Redis for caching?
Yes, Redis for session state and response caching. Plus I'm using the built-in memory provider from ElizaOS core for conversation context
Nice architecture! How many concurrent users can it handle?
We tested up to 1000 concurrent connections and it was still stable. The bottleneck is actually the LLM API calls, not our infrastructure
That's solid! Are you planning to add more models or stick with the current setup?
I want to experiment with some fine-tuned models. The generic responses are good but I think we can do better with domain-specific training
Definitely! Fine-tuning on your specific use case could make a huge difference in response quality
